news.title: Only 30% of MahaRERA recovery warrants executed; ₹527 crore still to be recovered
news.para: The slow progress contradicts revenue minister Chandrakant Bawankule's assurance during the state budget session, where he emphasised speedy execution of MahaRERA's recovery warrant orders and clearing the backlog within three months.

news.title: Noida: FIR filed against Supertech Cape Town AOA over not-functional STP
news.para: RP Singh, general manager (Jal), Noida Authority, said that inspections were conducted at the society on Friday, and it was found that the STP was not working as per the prescribed standard.

news.title: Delhi: Over 800 flats sold in just a month under Apna Ghar scheme
news.para: According to officials, 150 flats were sold in Loknayakpuram and 50 in Siraspur. "The positive momentum of the scheme is particularly evident in Narela, where all 115 EWS flats in Sector A1 A4 were fully booked. Additionally, MIG flats in Loknayakpuram are almost sold out," said an official.

news.title: Odisha HC orders bring shift in real estate sector, protect homebuyers’ interests
news.para: Hearing a plea from an allottee's association of a major housing project at Paikarapur in Kalinga Nagar, the Orissa HC brought a stay on the construction of an approach road by the developer to another of his projects since it was allegedly taken up in the common area of the existing housing project.

news.title: Lucknow: Ten FIRs against Ansal API in a day
news.para: Tanuja Krishna Dubey of Railway Officers' Colony, in her complaint said her late father booked a plot in 2011 and paid Rs 33.60 lakh by 2015.

news.title: Sand, laterite stone shortage hits construction industry in Dakshina Kannada
news.para: A lack of permits and strict law enforcement against illegal sand trade has also led to the shortage crisis. Meanwhile, laterite stone contractors are on strike against a steep hike in the fee for quarrying.

news.title: DDA to offer residential plots for auction in south Delhi area
news.para: DDA has issued a notice inviting tenders to select an experienced agency for the demarcation, along with developing the surrounding roads and services such as stormwater drains and the laying of pipelines for sewerage and water supply, said an official.

news.title: Margao property survey begins amid confusion
news.para: The survey is part of a state-wide geographical information system (GIS) mapping initiative to create a comprehensive digital property database for improved tax collection and municipal administration.

news.title: Goa town planning department clears housing projects without assessing water access
news.para: Clearances for towering housing colonies and luxury resorts are handed out without consultation with the public works department (PWD) or the water resources department (WRD), the very bodies tasked with ensuring that the state’s citizens are not left parched.

news.title: Over 11,000 homes built by Ranchi civic body under PMAY-Urban in 10 years
news.para: ​​The event highlighted RMC's progress in providing dignified homes under the national "Housing for All" mission. In ten years, RMC has completed 11,052 houses out of a sanctioned target of 12,587, achieving an 88% completion rate.

news.title: Mumbai court allows restoration of attached property worth ₹952 crore of Vadraj Cement
news.para: The ED, in a statement on Saturday, said this move is in continuation of its efforts to return properties to their rightful owners and enable financial institutions to monetise attached or seized assets.

news.title: ED attaches assets worth ₹557 crore of Mahira Group in money laundering case
news.para: The ED initiated the probe based on FIRs filed by Gurugram Police against M/s Sai Aaina Farms Pvt. Ltd. and others under various sections of the Indian Penal Code (IPC) related to cheating and forgery .

news.title: Construction and demolition waste plant to be inaugurated soon in Ludhiana
news.para: The construction and demolition (C&D) waste plant set up in Dhandhari was initially conceived under the Smart City Mission but was taken up under the Swachh Bharat Mission due to increase in its cost and change in the structure.

news.title: Over 150 unsafe buildings identified in Ludhiana
news.para: According to the fresh survey, zone D has the maximum number of unsafe buildings, which is 55, whereas zone A, which comprises the old city, has 48 unsafe buildings. Zone B and zone C have 21 and 35 unsafe buildings, respectively.

news.title: Ghaziabad development body frees ₹800 crore land for Indirapuram Extension project
news.para: A GDA official said the land parcel will be clubbed with the Indirapuram Extension scheme — covering an area of 34 hectares — where the development authority is planning a new township.

news.title: No homes on zudpi jungles will be demolished: Maharashtra revenue minister
news.para: Chairing a high-level meeting at Mantralaya to address the long standing issue, Bawankule warned senior officials from revenue and forest departments that delays in regularising such homes will not be tolerated.

news.title: Noida authority urges Uttar Pradesh government to review Gardenia Aims Developers' debt plan
news.para: The authority said that if allowed, the move would contradict a cabinet-approved policy for stalled projects, which requires defaulting builders to deposit 25% of dues before accessing relief measures.

news.title: Consumer forum fines GEAPL & Shriram Properties for eight-year flat delay in Vizag
news.para: The commission further directed Global Entropolis Asia Pvt Ltd (GEAPL) and Shriram Properties Pvt Ltd to register and deliver the fully furnished 2,011 sq ft flat to the complainant.

news.title: Delhi civic body extends 10% property tax rebate till July 31
news.para: The meeting was chaired by Satya Sharma, the newly appointed Chairperson of the Standing Committee, and saw active participation from all members, who discussed a wide range of issues concerning public welfare.
